cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with improving the performance of mobile data traffic by pushing popular content to cheap "helper" nodes during off-peak hours. This involves caching and recommending related content to users. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes efficient algorithms and analyzes the expected gains, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper deals with video content, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
